programme.title: Rye's Redemption Buck, The BEST Big Buck Moments From 2024
programme.desc: On this week's episode, we round out the 2024 deer hunting season with a bang as Rye Ludwig tags a great River Farm buck on the second to last day of the year. Taking us through the lessons learned, relationships made and memories that will last a lifetime, Rye discusses his takeaways from the fall and what ultimately led to tagging yet another River Farm buck before the final bell toll of Iowa's deer season. After that, we take you along through a highlight that encapsulates the action packed 2024 season and widespread success and memories made that the team experienced this year. From all of us here at Midwest Whitetail, we sincerely hope you enjoyed this season and can't wait to bring future stories to life here on the channel. Be sure to follow our YouTube and other social media channels for updates throughout the coming weeks as we look to 2025 and more memories to come. Thank you for watching!

programme.title: Iowa Giant At The Buzzer, Justin And Drake's Epic Hunting Season
programme.desc: On this week's episode of Midwest Whitetail, we kick things off with Mike Reed who wastes no time getting back out to the River Farm following the close of Iowa's deer season. With the goal of keeping tabs on the deer herd and also providing them with excellent nutrition moving forward into the coldest months of the year, Mike gets his Ax One Complete Feed from our good friends at @axoutdoors7116 out on multiple locations on the farm and discusses the benefit that the product can yield for you. From there, we join Justin Karns who takes us along for the journey of his epic 2024 deer season with partner in crime Drake Lamb. Together, the duo logged big buck encounter after big buck encounter that included a once in a lifetime close range sighting of an Iowa monarch locked down with a doe and a giant up and comer on Justin's treasured home farm. Utilizing one of many food plots implemented at the home farm, the encounter encapsulated years of hard work improving the ground his family calls home. Down to the final days of season, the guys pushed forward and showed that the grind always pays off with Justin tagging a great buck and rounding out an incredible 2024 deer hunting journey. As always, we thank you for joining us on another episode of Midwest Whitetail and we hope you enjoy the show!

programme.title: Surprise Giant 8 Hits The Ground, First Buck Of 2025
programme.desc: On this week's episode we are back in Iowa kicking off 2025 in a big way. After less than stellar weather all shotgun season, frigid cold has graced the Midwest prompting some great hunting. Heading back to the bottom plot, Mike and Bella Reed are hoping to finally lay eyes on an ancient buck known as "Anna's Buck." Right away, a giant surprise buck hits the field well before legal shooting time when the duo notice something is off. Carrying a major leg injury, Bella makes a perfect shot on the giant 8 and fills a second tag by the time the evening ends. Putting the stamp on her greatest season yet, we couldn't be happier for her and look forward to seeing what the rest of the late season has in store. As always, thanks for watching another episode of Midwest Whitetail!
